history.content:
": I was wondering if my previously approved time conflict would allow me to still get off the 162 waitlist? "

While I'm not certain, I doubt it.

For the new system, do approved time conflict requests allow getting off the waitlist for a class when there's conflicts for the waitlisted section? 

I waitlisted CS162 in Phase II, and also enrolled in Econ131 by completing and getting approved a time conflict request (since the two classes' lectures conflicted). Today, I dropped and re-added myself to the waitlist for 162 to switch to the new section, but my 162 section now also conflicts with my Econ131 section. Based on Michael David-Sasson's post today, I need to not have any conflicts for my 162 section in order to be able to be enrolled.

So, I was wondering if my previously approved time conflict would allow me to still get off the 162 waitlist? Or do I have to switch out to another Econ131 section (resolve only the section conflict), or drop Econ131 completely (resolve both the section and lecture conflict) in order to enrolled in 162?
history.subject: Getting of the waitlist with section conflict + time conflict approval
